### 2. Build real authentication (login/signup)
**Deferred from:** Step 2 — Data model design (`user` table)
**Why:** Avoiding two hard, unrelated problems (data modeling + auth security) at the same time. The `user` table exists now with a `password_hash` placeholder column, populated later.
**Revisit at:** After core Card/Collection features work end-to-end using one manually-inserted test user. At that point, implement real signup/login (decide: email+password with hashing, vs. OAuth) and replace the placeholder test user with real account creation.

